Adding slave in Jenkins Master:
Manage Jenkins -->Manage Nodes -->New Node--> give a node name --> click on permananent agent --> ok-->give remote root directory --> 
launch method: launch slave via agent ssh -->Host: give Ip add(ip add can be obtained by a command ifconfig)-->can add credentials 
After that click on the node or the slave that you cretaed and open logs to check the output.
To check if the slave is added to master.
Give the command: sudo ls  /home/edureka/
Shows that the slave is sucessfully added to master.
